  "text": "We shall set κ = 1. The ten form is given in terms of its nine form potential by F (10) = 10dA (9) . Varying A (9) gives M = const. and varying M gives F (10) = 10Me 5φ/2 η (10) where η [CITATION_1] is the volume form of the spacetime. Note that varying the metric does not affect the final term. Therefore the Einstein equations are the same as those for which the only matter is a scalar field φ with potential",
